[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing test coverage issues**\n\nI’m considering whether the reporter excludes certain call sites when a test class loads a class directly by name. It seems coverage should still be present. Also, the method name \"class$\" has a dollar sign, which could be a factor, but findStatic works. I wonder if there's an UnsupportedFeatureError in the native code due to private method handles, or if existing tests are failing without compiling. There’s also a chance the dynamic-access report was generated before our file.\n\n**Contemplating reflection methods**\n\nI’m thinking about whether the \"caller frame\" in the instrumented Class#forName counts as a helper when the method is invoked reflectively. It does, but what if MethodHandle is being invoked as native direct and isn’t instrumented? That feels weird. I could try mimicking MapCreator using `java.lang.reflect.Method` instead. I’d need to import Method, remove method handles, and use getDeclaredMethod to invoke. Even though direct reflection isn’t allowed by project rules, existing tests seem to allow it. I might also consider passing the closure class's own name instead of a String.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00e1d1a0b06d4d40016a27400153d081939751d650188e65f9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ0AX-YUeZvNwy9lBCliViMn5u6ftZL-K6SbjQMx3zDJ40qvBcRjTyqbSiNFJIUzqBf_u7T-fdZfsMcfa5F3Ou0AA7atyBOML9NHpi8SljzMyc2BAdQONWFcmPQGnt3zS2OeYf4iL66-5unXaJwauG_MeOMqFVKSSiCX6QObTZXgDGKIoB6Plxpkvq48Zrdd7hh_2Pxh4YQ-H4flUord7tTLLOdQi5J6U6O3ZLkwdjrVOqfGK2MOnU-fcR7Rhow77K270JhMoomrpAulVfQLfm6yc3srdQGW8RIT9S1vBev37CGJUo8AsY1Vq2fMi_zefYljlzoV1AWXaP4VcrNC227JshzozfPMcbIb7erUergbeCBbuw13nDU-Mkur_Q45q2WMlwySs58x8qatEEoF8wpLsjvT7yBxArU_humx0qcRvuq_g42ACVF0lBMLbhSp0bq8tCDX4e8jcrF__UBDAy3E2AduKXxJLMSCL2iqSm-e9_JSPkzPjYOBXydLk2JI2SROA_wMo6cYRxUUVeAoheredTdS1kZoJRuXhUSjS5oVI72xRqt3cnTZYr1h5RoOWtN